I just listened to this, and though I may get voted off the island for
this opinion, like so much of Goldsmith's output post-1990, I just
don't get the fuss that surrounds this score. It's dominated by a
nice lyrical melody that Goldsmith very nicely pounds into our
heads, and...well, it's just &quot;nice&quot;. It never really rises to anything
or plumbs any particular depths. This is yet another of the long list
of scores from Goldsmith's late era which I believe would not be
held in nearly as high esteem had it been written by some guy
named Frank Friggleheimer.

Oh well...I'll always have &quot;The Wind and the Lion&quot;.
</POST>
