It fascinates me that a majority of collectors 'hate' this NEMESIS
score. I've seen the film several times on the big screen and have the
dvd. The music Goldsmith wrote for a number of specific scenes is
brilliant. All of the music for the final third of the film is spot
on. Unfortunately, Varese only released 45 minutes of the score
leaving out a huge chunk of excellent music. Fortunately, I have the 2
disc recording sessions of the score and all that wonderful music is
included. Tense action scoring that takes no prisoners. That builds
and builds with intensity, leading up to the fateful ramming of the
saucer section into the enemy craft. All that music is grand and super
thrilling. A solid B effort from Goldsmith. The music won't rank as
some of his best action scoring but it sure as hell isn't the turkey
everyone who hates the score would have you believe.
